The paper addresses the problem of speech enhancement using deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SD), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks and sequence-to-sequence learning also suggests the sub-category of structured inference (cs.SI). The focus on multichannel speech enhancement further narrows down the sub-categories to those related to audio and speech processing.
